It's doing a recursive post-order traversal of the tree, accumulating a and o. Let's see the recursive code: Java:

 static int maxMatching(int v, int p) {
        int a = 0;
        int o = 0;
        for (int w : g[v]) {
            if (w == p) continue;
            int r = maxMatching(w, v);
            a += r / 2;
            o += r % 2;
        }
        return 2 * a + Math.min(1, o) + 1;
    }

 Functions returns a value for a node v, with parent p. So for each neighbor w of v (excluding p), recurse, then handle the returned value r.

After collecting the children's contributions, a stays as sum r//2 (integer division), o is sum r mod 2 (the remainder).

